Developing and Testing on macOS

Since you are developing on a MacBook, ensure that all dependencies and instructions are compatible with macOS.

Homebrew Package Manager

Install Homebrew if you haven’t already:

/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

Install PostgreSQL

brew install postgresql

Install Qt and PyQt

You can install PyQt5 via pip, but installing Qt separately ensures that Qt Designer and other tools are available.

	•	Install Qt:
Download and install Qt from the official website.
	•	Install PyQt5:

pip install PyQt5



Install Other Dependencies

As per the requirements.txt.

Notes

	•	Testing: Regularly run tests in the tests/ directory to ensure your code works as expected.
	•	Version Control: Commit changes often with meaningful commit messages.
	•	Documentation: Keep the docs/ directory updated with any changes in features or usage.
